Description


Reviews (0)



Product Description
Viewing this VideoWe recommend using Quicktime to view this downloadable video. Please visit http://www.apple.com/Quicktime/ to download and install the latest version of Quicktime onto your computer.

Prof. Michael H. Hart’s speech given at the Second American Renaissance Conference in 1996. Prof. Hart outlines a practical means of dividing the United States into voluntary racial and non-racial states.


Second American Renaissance Conference (1996)
Louisville, Kentucky


The 1996 AR Conference was ground-breaking in several respects. The Civil Rights Industry, Inc. and the newsmedia sought—for the first, but not the last time—to have it cancelled or moved. It also was the proof that the talented and high-quality presentations of 1994 could be repeated.






